com.brookes.aepsi.webservices.reference
Interface IDataExchange

public interface IDataExchange

IDataExchange -- Interface defining the web services to implement data exchange.

Exposes five methods to validate, get a count of children, get a list of child guids, get exchange-format XML for each child in a list, and update child data from the exchange format. This is a copy of the interface as defined in the AEPSI source code.

Copyright (c) 2008 by Brookes Publishers, Inc.

Author:
Steve Carton (steve.carton@retrievalsystems.com)

getChildList

java.lang.String getChildList(java.lang.String credentials)
                              throws com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException
getChildList - Returns an XML document as a String that has a list of the GUIDs for all the children in this account.

The XML is in the form:
<aepsi><guid>147</guid><guid>139</guid><guid>55</guid></aepsi>

Parameters:
credentials - - the credentials returned from a call to getCredentials.
Returns:
- the XML list of GUIDS
Throws:
com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException

getChildren

java.lang.String getChildren(java.lang.String credentials,
                             java.lang.String list)
                             throws com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException
getChildren - Returns the export XML for each child identified by a guid element in the list.

If the list of GUIDS is null or empty, then all children (with GUIDS) for this program are exported.

The list is a String of xml in the same form as above (getChildList).
The resulting XML is in this format:
<children><child> <family_name>Villegas Rodriguez</family_name> <given_name>Gregorio</given_name> <address1>2415 N. Huston Ave.</address1> <city>Grand Island</city> <state>NE</state> <zip>68803</zip> <classroom>Partc</classroom> <local_id1>3954342596</local_id1> <guid>147</guid> <dob>2003-05-05</dob> <pre_weeks>0</pre_weeks> <gender>M</gender> <level>1</level> <dev_status>Dev. Delay or Disability</dev_status> </children>

Parameters:
credentials - - the credentials returned from a call to getCredentials.
list - - the list of GUIDS in the above format.
Returns:
- the XML of the retrieved child records as a String.
Throws:
com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException

putChildren

java.lang.String putChildren(java.lang.String credentials,
                             java.lang.String children)
                             throws com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException
putChildren - updates the AEPSI database with the children in the "children" XML string.

Source must be a valid XML source (see the DTD).

Parameters:
credentials - - the credentials returned from a call to getCredentials.
children - - the valid XML stream of children
Returns:
- a report in XML format of the results of the import.
Throws:
com.brookes.aepsi.exception.AEPSIException
